{title: Lady In A Blue Mercedes}
{artist: Johnny Duncan
and Janie Fricke}
{composer: Written by Daniel Darst and Gary Gentry}

Parked her car [G7]down by the [C]sea
She stepped into the sand and [G]took me by the hand
And we [D7]traveled away in my [G]dreams
And we drank [C]Pina Coladas down in Puerto Rico
We tangoed in Montego [G]Bay
We [D7]sipped Champaign in the summer rain
On a warm Caribbean [G]day
I put a [C]pretty flower in her long black hair
Along the sands of Waiki[G]ki
And [D7]I left my heart in San Francisco
Where she first made love to [G]me

Then I awoke to the sound of the tide coming in
And the sun was almost [D7]gone
I didn't want to wake from my beautiful dream
But I had to take it on [G]home
Then somewhere in the evening came a heavenly voice
Saying thank you for a wonderful [C]day
Then the beautiful lady in the [G]blue Mercedes
Blew a [D7]kiss and drove [G]away
Repeat #3
We stuffed our [C]pockets full of pretty shells
While the trade winds blew all [G]night
We [D7]bought mangos and bananas in the market place
And made love by the fire [G]light
Repeat #3